                <h1>Effortlessly Make Backgrounds Transparent in Paint</h1>
                <p>To make a background transparent in Paint, first open your image. Select the 'Magic Select' tool to outline the area you want to keep. After adjusting the selection, click 'Next' and then 'Done.' You can now cut the selected image and paste it into a new canvas, which will allow you to save it with a transparent background as a PNG file.</p>
